Paper and board production and fibrous materials consumed in the manufacture of paper and board, 1965-1999

Dataset containing consumption and production statistics for various board and paper products. Units are specified below.

pietc_pbfm

Format

A data frame with 56 observations of 19 variables:

Years
Years
Prod.PaperBoard
Prod.PaperBoard. Paper and Paperboard Production, in 1000 Tons
Consump.Tot
Total Consumption of Fibrous Materials, in 1000 Tons
Consump.WoodPulp
Consumption of Woodpulp, in 1000 Tons
Consump.RecPaper
Consumption of Recovered Paper, in 1000 Tons
Consump.Other
Consumption of Other Fibrous Materials, in 1000 Tons
Consump.PerTonProd.Tot
Total Consumption of Fibrous Material per ton of Paper and Board Produced, in Tons
Consump.PerTonProd.WoodPulp
Consumption of Wood pulp per ton of Paper and Board Produced, in Tons
Consump.PerTonProd.RecPaper
Consumption of Recovered Paper per ton of Paper and Board Produced, in Tons
Consump.PerTonProd.Other
Consumption of Other Fibrous Materials per ton of Paper and Board Produced, in Tons
RagsOther.RecPaperUtiRatePerc
Rags and Other: Recovered Paper Utilization Rate Percent
RagsOther.Prod.Estimated
Rags and Other: Estimated Production, in Thousand Tons
RagsOther.Imports.Estimated
Rags and Other: Estimated Imports, in Thousand Tons
RagsOther.Exports.Estimated
Rags and Other: Estimated Exports, in Thousand Tons

Source

American Paper Institute, American Forest & Paper Association: Statistics of Paper, Paperboard & Wood Pulp
